text: Jung Ho-young (Korean: 정호영; RR: Jeong Ho-yeong; born 23 August 2001) is a South Korean female professional volleyball player. She also competed at the 2018 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship. == References == == Other websites == * FIVB profile * jung-hoyoung globalsportsarchive.com Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean volleyball players
